          <td valign="top" width="1" ><img src="/magic/gfx/trans.gif" width="18" height="2" vspace="0" hspace="0" border="0"></td>
          <td  valign="top"><!-- #BeginEditable "Body" --> 
            <BR><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td><font class="h1font"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="96a39077dee2ab4e469526538c236f78" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
<tr height="10"><td width="98%" bgcolor="#333333" height="10"><img src="/magic/gfx/trans.gif" width="6" height="2" vspace="0" hspace="0" border="0"></td><td valign="bottom" align="right"><img src="/magic/gfx/hrz/tk.gif" width="103" height="10" border="0" vspace="0" hspace="0"></td>
</tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td valign="top" align="right">
<img src="/magic/gfx/hrz/bk.gif" width="92" height="24" border="0" vspace="0" hspace="0"></td>
</tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Invincibility soud interesting to you?<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/magic/gfx/star2.gif" width="20" height="20" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magic/gfx/star2.gif" width="20" height="20" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magic/gfx/star2.gif" width="20" height="20" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magic/gfx/star2.gif" width="20" height="20" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.20)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/magic/main/mpage.php?member=6207'>Patrick "Wittens Hand" Dennis</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/magic/main/mpage.php?member=6207&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> August 15, 2002</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> The &#8220;I*m invincible and there is nothing you can do about it combo&#8221; Has long been sought out. I have made a recent breakthrough that will not only make you invincible, but also lock your opponent out on hurting you for much longer. Life and cards will not matter anymore, as when this combo is set up you will have anything you could ever want in a deck. Intrigued yet? Well my little brain has been working overtime on this little thing and I*m proud to express that the invincible player combo is indeed possible.<br />
<br />
It all starts out like this. You need to make sure any damage they do wont affect you so you can win the game. So the first card is one many people will play anyways. Here it goes:<br />
<br />
Transcendence		3WWW<br />
<br />
Enchantment<br />
<br />
You do not lose the game for having less than 0 life. If at anytime you have more than 20 life you lose the game. If you would lose life instead gain 2 life. (Damage Dealt causes you to lose life)<br />
<br />
Great card on its own isn*t it? You are invincible. The only problem is that stupid life gain. What if there was a way to not gain life and make me really invincible? Well this card is called Forsaken Wastes!<br />
<br />
Forsaken Wastes	2B<br />
<br />
Enchant World<br />
<br />
No player can gain life. During each player*s upkeep, that player loses one life. If Forsaken Wastes is successfully targeted by a spell the spells controller loses five life.<br />
<br />
OK so it not only locks in the game, but also has an effect that I like to call &#8220;End Game&#8221;. End Game is the principle that means that if left unchecked for too long will kill and opponent. The other meaning of it is simple. If it makes play, your opponent better have a counter strategy right there, or they are dead the next turn or such depending on the End Game. This combo locks in the game by not allowing life gain, then doing damage each upkeep. Throw in our transcendence and you have an invincible combo. But just being invincible alone will not allow us to crush our opponent. No that would be stupid to assume that merely being invincible can kill an opponent. If they disenchant you need a backup plan. That plan is to use your newfound invincibility to draw up cards. How you say? Necropotence shows us the answer yet again!<br />
<br />
Necropotence		BBB<br />
<br />
Enchantment<br />
<br />
Skip your draw phase. If you discard a card from your hand, remove that card from the game. 0: Pay 1 life to set aside the top card of your library. At the beginning of your next discard phase, put that card into your hand. Effects that prevent or redirect damage cannot be used to counter this loss of life.<br />
<br />
Pay life draw up cards. Hmmm sounds risky if you are at a low life anyways. But wait, I*m invincible! Lets draw up some cards and fill my hand. Then I*ll play the cards I need to play to win the game! Sounds like a winner. Add a couple of fountain watches to make your enchantments untargetable. Maybe splash blue for diplomatic immunities and counters and you got a fair deck. The obvious question is why post such a game breaking combo?<br />
<br />
My friends I live a cursed life. Ask me how to do something and within a couple of minutes I could probably tell you. I have long been working on such a combo in a few of cards as possible. This is the result a two-card combo that locks you in as invincible to all but the almighty disenchant and tranquility.<br />
<br />
I leave you with this combo. Use it for peace folks, not war. *Bursts out laughing*<br />
